{"lemma":"قَطَرَ","slug":"قَطَرَ","root":"ق.ط.ر","root_slug":"ق-ط-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ط-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَطَرَ","root":"قطر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":10,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35892"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drip, to dribble, to trickle","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"الْحَنَفِيَّةُ فِي الْمَطْبَخِ تَقْطُرُ، مِمَّا يَهْدِرُ الْمَاءُ كُلَّ يَوْمٍ.","english":"The faucet in the kitchen drips, wasting water every day."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let drip, to let dribble, to infuse in driblets","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قَطَرَ الدَّوَاءَ فِي عَيْنَيْهِ.","english":"He dripped the medicine into his eyes."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let drip, to let dribble, to infuse in driblets","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"قَطَّرَ الدَّوَاءَ فِي عَيْنَيْهِ.","english":"He dripped the medicine into his eyes."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to filter, to refine, to distill"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to form a train of camels, to line up camels in single file (connected with halters)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to couple, to tow, to tug"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to throw down, to deject"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fumigate with agarwood (قُطُر (quṭur))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drops, dribblets; rain","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"syrup","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَطَرَ (qaṭara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dripping, dribbling, trickling"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trailer"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"region, quarter, district, section, zone, tract, country, land"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diameter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diagonal"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"caliber, bore"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Qatar (a country in West Asia in the Middle East)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"agalloch, agarwood, aloeswood, eaglewood; Aquilaria malaccensis (syn. Aquilaria agallocha)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of قِطَار (qiṭār)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fusible copper or brass","examples":[{"text":"آتُونِي زُبَرَ الْحَدِيدِ حَتَّىٰ إِذَا سَاوَىٰ بَيْنَ الصَّدَفَيْنِ قَالَ ٱنْفُخُوا حَتَّىٰ إِذَا جَعَلَهُ نَارًا قَالَ آتُونِي أُفْرِغْ عَلَيْهِ قِطْرًا","english":"“Give me bits of iron.” Until he dumped equally high between the two mountain cuttings. He said: “Blow.” Till he made fire. He said: “Bring me molten copper I pour upon it.“"},{"text":"وَأَسَلْنَا لَهُ عَيْنَ الْقِطْرِ","english":"We made the spring of molten copper flow for him."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of streaked fabric"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35892","headword_ar":"قَطَرَ","root":"qTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTorN","text_ar":"قَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaraAnN","text_ar":"قَطَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTuwrN","text_ar":"قُطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [and in an intensive sense,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoTaArN","text_ar":"تَقْطَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gusolN","text_ar":"غُسْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":");] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqTr","text_ar":"اقطر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqATr","text_ar":"تقاطر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) said of water, (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) and of tears, (K,) or other fluid, (S, * TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It dropped, dripped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell in drops;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it flowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drop by drop."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  It occurs in a trad. as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara EaraqFA","text_ar":"قَطَرَ عَرَقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawolFA","text_ar":"بَوْلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He let fall sweat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urine, in drops,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in which each subst, is in the accus. case as a specificative: said of a person in intense awe or fear. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara AlS~amogu minaY","text_ar":"قَطَرَ الصَّمْغُ مِنَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ajarapi","text_ar":"الشَّجَرَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The gum"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exuded in drops"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came forth from the tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTarati A@sotuhu","text_ar":"قَطَرَتِ ا@سْتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSalat","text_ar":"مَصَلَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His anus voided excrement in drops"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"قَطَرَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTuwrN","text_ar":"قُطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away into the country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and hastened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTara","text_ar":"مَطَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTuwrN","text_ar":"مُطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTarahu","text_ar":"قَطَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, Mgh, Msb, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTorN","text_ar":"قَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqTrhu","text_ar":"اقطرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqoTaArN","text_ar":"اـِقْطَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or the latter but not the former accord. to AZ; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qT~rhu","text_ar":"قطّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoTiyrN","text_ar":"تَقْطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, K, or a man, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely water &c.) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to drop, drip, dribble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fall in drops;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to flow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drop by drop:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he poured it out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTarotu AlmaA='a fiY AlHaloqi","text_ar":"قَطَرْتُ المَا=ءَ فِى الحَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqoTarotuhu","text_ar":"اَقْطَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaT~arotuhu","text_ar":"قَطَّرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the water to fall drop by drop into the throat."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA qaTaraka EalayonaA","text_ar":"مَا قَطَرَكَ عَلَيْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What hath poured thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Sab~aka","text_ar":"مَا صَبَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon us?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara","text_ar":"قَطَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTorN","text_ar":"قَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prostrated such a one with vehemence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K.) [Perhaps this is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quTorN","text_ar":"قُطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying the “ side; ” and if so it is not tropical. See also 2.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara Alv~awoba","text_ar":"قَطَرَ الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sewed the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara AlA_ibila","text_ar":"قَطَرَ الاـِبِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTorN","text_ar":"قَطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qT~rhA","text_ar":"قطّرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoTiyrN","text_ar":"تَقْطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) but this has an intensive signification; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqTrhA","text_ar":"اقطرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) but this [says SM] I do not find in the [other] lexicons; Az and ISd mention only the first and second; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disposed the camels in a file, string,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"series;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he placed the camels near, one to another, in a file, string,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"series;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and tied the halter of each, except the first, to the tail of the next before it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is said in a proverb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljalaba","text_ar":"الجَلَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ufaADu yaqaT~iru","text_ar":"النُّفَاضُ يَقَطِّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The failure of provisions causes the camels, driven or brought from one place to another, to be disposed in files for sale."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTara AlbaEiyra","text_ar":"قَطَرَ البَعِيرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He smeared the camel with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiraAn","text_ar":"قَطِرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","As","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}